				 Policy meet today
				 	 Raja																								New Delhi, Oct. 2 (PTI): Communications minister A. Raja has convened a meeting of all telecom operators tomorrow to discuss the broad industry scenario and a host of policy issues. 																								The meeting comes a couple of days after the deadline for submitting licence applications expired on October 1. 																								Two representatives from each operator are allowed to attend the meeting, which does not have any fixed agenda except to discuss the telecom situation, sources said. However, the issue of fresh licences could come up for discussion, they added.																								The DoT has received close to 500 applications for telecom licences, including from AT amp;T, DLF, Unitech, Parsvnath, Omaxe, Videocon and Sterlite. 
